Summary of ASX Announcement:

Company: Mayur Resources Limited (ASX: MRL)
Announcement Type: Project Development Update

Material Information:

  • Central Lime Project (CLP) Progress:
  • Phase 2 wharf completed – enables roll-on/roll-off (RO/RO) vessel access and bulk cargo handling.
  • Phase 3 wharf construction underway (9-month timeline) to accommodate Handymax-class ocean-going vessels.
  • Bulk earthworks commenced, including drill/blast operations for Quicklime kiln bench.

  • Geotechnical investigations ongoing for bridges and 27.6km service road (critical logistics link).

  • Procurement & Logistics:

  • Long-lead items ordered (fuel storage, desalination plant, construction equipment).

  • Civil construction equipment (excavators, trucks, graders, etc.) expected on-site Q3 CY2025.

  • Infrastructure Expansion:

  • New Port Moresby office opened to support project ramp-up (capacity: ~50 staff).

No capital/financial figures or trading-sensitive dates disclosed. No material valuation or liquidity impacts noted beyond project execution updates.

Summary of ASX Announcement (Clinical Trial Update - Translational Data):

  • CHM CDH17 CAR-T cells demonstrated persistence up to 6 months post-infusion in 2/4 subjects at Dose Level 1 (phase 1/2 trial).
  • Target validation: Cadherin 17 (CDH17) confirmed on tumour cells in all subjects.
  • Trial progress: Dose Level 2 enrolment ongoing; Phase 1 aims to enrol up to 15 patients.
  • Trial design: Phase 1/2 focuses on advanced GI cancers (colorectal, gastric, neuroendocrine tumours).

No material financial/capital impact identified. Pure clinical update with no fundraising, timelines, or operational metrics.

Material Information Summary (ASM - Heap Leach Metallurgical Testwork Results)

  • Key Recovery Rates:
  • HLC-West Composite (first 8-10 years of ore):
    • Nd: up to 80%
    • Pr: up to 85%
    • Tb: up to 44%
    • Dy: up to 38%

  • Optimal crush size: 12.5–25 mm (reduces costs).

  • Process Efficiency:

  • Heap leaching simplifies flowsheet vs. traditional methods, potentially lowering capital/operating costs.
  • Eliminates need for energy-intensive roasting in initial phase.

Location: Dubbo Project (NSW)

  • Next Steps:
  • Heap Leach Scoping Study (due early Q3 2025).

  • Column leaching testwork to commence late June 2025 (results H2 2025).

  • Strategic Impact:

  • Phased development approach could accelerate REE production (focusing on Nd/Pr/Tb/Dy oxides first).
  • Supports offtake/funding discussions due to lower upfront costs.

No capital raising, financials, or timetable changes disclosed.

Summary of Material Information:

Farm-In & Joint Venture Agreement Highlights:
- Parties: Dart Mining NL (DTM) enters agreement with Great Divide Mining (GDM) for the Coonambula Antimony-Gold Project (Central Queensland).
- Earn-In Structure:
- Stage 1: Dart earns 15% interest via immediate payment of AUD 250,000.
- Stage 2: Dart can earn additional 36% (total 51%) by completing 4,000m drilling and delivering JORC resource estimates within 26 months.
- Drilling incentive: 1% interest per 133.3m drilled.
- Resource incentive: 3% per annual JORC-compliant resource/exploration target.
- Key Project Data:
- High-grade intersections from historic drilling:
- 3m @ 9.18% Sb, 6m @ 5.12% Sb & 1.55g/t Au, 3m @ 8.53g/t Au.
- Surface samples: Rock chips up to 44.9% Sb, trenching up to 6.15g/t Au + 3.1% Sb.
- IP Survey: Govt-funded (CEI grant) to commence within 3 months; targets high-grade Sb-Au zones.
- Exploration Plan:
- Year 1: 2,000m infill drilling at Banshee Mine for JORC resource.
- Year 2: 2,000m drilling to expand targets (Perseverance gold mine, strike extensions).

Capital Impact:
- No immediate capital raising; Dart funds exploration via AUD 250k payment and operational commitments.
- Potential future dilutionary risk if Dart fails to meet earn-in milestones (GDM buy-out option at fair market value).

Next Steps:
- IP survey (Q3 2025), heritage assessments, and infill drilling at Banshee.

Valuation Relevance:
- Exposure to high-grade Sb-Au project in proximity to major deposits (e.g., Cracow gold mine).
- Potential resource definition catalyst within 12–24 months.

Omitted: Operational details, historical commentary, non-material geology.

Material Information Summary (Farm-Out Agreement):
- Completed farm-out agreement with Dart Mining NL (DTM) for GDM's Coonambula Project (includes historic Banshee Antimony Mine).
- Terms:
- DTM acquires 15% stake (6 tenements) for $250,000 cash (paid within 5 business days).
- Can extend to 51% by funding 4,000m drilling + 2 geological reports over 2 years.
- DTM appointed as Manager of Coonambula JV; will oversee Queensland government-funded IP geophysics program at Banshee Mine.
- Strategic impact: Advances GDM’s shift from explorer to producer, focusing on near-term cash flow.
